data.description: You will be so impressed by this immaculate & pristine 4 bedroom 3-1/2 bath home with over 3000 square feet of living space situated on a professionally landscaped corner lot in the highly desirable Heartland Circle subdivision w/ walking trails and walking distance to the "Rocketship" park with playground.  Discover the perfect blend of style and functionality in this home with not ONE but TWO primary retreats! You will fall in love with this open concept floor plan.   As you step inside you will be greeted by a large two-story foyer adjacent to a spacious living room (which is currently used as an office) and a formal dining room.   The gourmet eat-in kitchen with its light creamed cabinets, sleek white granite countertops, stainless steel appliances and center island is perfect for the culinary chef who enjoys creating those savory feasts for the family.  The seamless flow from the breakfast area into the adjacent, spacious family room makes entertaining your guests and loved ones a breeze. Behind the family room awaits the main floor primary suite which is a perfect in-law arrangement with its own convenient walk-in closet and its own private en-suite w/ lovely soaker tub & separate shower.  The second floor features incredible living space including a huge loft complete with large walk-in closet for storage space, a pool table and plenty of room for lounging. There is also a bonus room (19X11)  w/ vaulted ceilings which can be converted into a fifth bedroom, currently framed and insulated.  Seller is leaving the new drywall, new hardwood flooring, recessed lights and electrical outlets for this room.  The second primary suite features vaulted ceilings, a large walk-in closet and private lux bath. Generous room sizes for bedrooms #3 & #4. Don't miss the first floor laundry room and heated three car garage. Please exclude the freezer in the garage. Additional 1,627 square feet in full, unfinished basement w/ roughed- in plumbing is ready for your finishing touches or to keep as a huge storage area.  Recent updates: new light fixtures in foyer, dining room & bathrooms (2023), new microwave (Dec 2023), All trim, baseboards, doors, banisters, stairs and railings have been recently painted. Neutral walls throughout, and most have newer paint.  Check out the backyard and enjoy those upcoming BBQ's on the brick paver patio and watch the kiddos play in the backyard or chalk on the walking trail. This beauty is so close to everything: shopping, great downtown restaurants, the Fox River, yearly festivals, local parks and Raging Waves waterpark. Fall in love with the hometown feel of Yorkville! Make this one yours! Welcome Home!
